  "prompt": "Can Windex leach through aquarium glass?",
  "response": "Windex and similar glass cleaning products typically contain ammonia and other chemicals that can be harmful to fish and other aquatic life. While it is unlikely that Windex would leach through aquarium glass, there is still a risk if the product comes into direct contact with the aquarium or its water.\n\nIt's important to avoid using any cleaning products that are not specifically designed for aquariums or are made for use around fish. If you need to clean aquarium glass, it is best to use products that are safe for aquarium use or simply use water and a sponge, or a specialized aquarium glass cleaner.\n\nIf Windex were to accidentally come into contact with the aquarium or its equipment, it is advisable to perform a water change and thoroughly rinse any surfaces that may have been contaminated before reintroducing any pets or plants.",
